{{ja-kanjitab|あに|yomi=k}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=あに|-}} of unclear derivation:
* Probably originally a compound of {{compound|ja|吾|tr1=a|pos1=Eastern Old Japanese first-person pronoun|の|tr2=no|pos2=possessive particle|兄|tr3=ye → e|t3=[[eldest]] [[sibling]]|pos3=see below}}:
*: {{IPAfont|⟨a no<sub>2</sub> ye⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/anʉʲɨe/}} → {{IPAchar|/ani/}}
* Alternatively, an [[apophony|apophonic]] form of {{m|ja|姉|tr=ane||[[elder]] [[sister]]}}, itself from the same derivation above, possibly by fusion with empathic particle {{ja-r|い}}.

